Residents in Barcelona fed up with the hordes of tourists crowding their streets have taken their protest against mass tourism to one of the city's most famous landmarks.

Around 300 people organised a noisy demonstration around the Sagrada Familia to complain about the holidaymakers make their lives a misery.

One protester, Abel Maruny, said: 'I'm fed up with being elbowed. I'm not a rude person but at times I run out of patience.'

