Neighbour Mireia Daniel, 40, added: 'The last few years have been terrible. I can't even take my son to his nursery in a pushchair.'

The number of tourists visiting Barcelona has more than tripled in the last 20 years.

More than three million people visit the Sagrada Familia, a large Roman Catholic church and Unesco World Heritage site designed by Catalan architect Antoni Gaudi, every year.

